          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(center)">COPY</p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                                        <date>Dec. 31. 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Friend</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">I send you again a few subscribers to the
                                        “Occident”<lb/> which I have procured since my last of the
                                                  <date>15<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst.</p>
                              <p/>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I also send you 8 copies of the “Alta California”
                                        and the “Whig”, which<lb/> contains several items of
                                        discussion upon the observance of the <date>Sabbath</date>
                                        &amp;c,<lb/> by the perusal of which, you will notice that
                                        we do not allow our Religion to<lb/> be slandered, even out
                                        here on these Western shores, &amp; are always ready to<lb/>
                                        defend our proud and sacred Faith. You'll read the articles
                                        (I marked them<lb/> with a black rounding) &amp; form then
                                        your own idea about them. There has nothing<lb/> else,
                                        concerning Jewish affairs, transpired to my knowledge; I
                                        shall always<lb/> endeavor to keep you posted up on any
                                        thing of any importance to you, that<lb/> may occur here,
                                        &amp; which may serve as interesting news in your
                                        Occident.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The Rainy Season is very severe this year, beyond
                                        all expectations, &amp; it is for<lb/> that reason that
                                        Merchants did fail in laying in sufficient supplies for<lb/>
                                        the winter, and the consequence is in some mines, that
                                        miners have to suffer<lb/> very much for want of provisions.
                                        For all other local affairs I refer you to<lb/> the
                                        Papers.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I enjoy, thank God, good health &amp; hope you may
                                        enjoy the same Blessing;<lb/> but Business has moderated
                                        greatly, yet we console ourselves with bright<lb/>
                                        prospects.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Let me soon hear from you again. Accept the best
                                        wishes for your<lb/> Health and Happiness</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">from</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">Yours Truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">(signed)  <persName role="author">C. H.
                                                  Meyer</persName></p>
                              <p/>
                              <p>N. B. <persName>Mr. Roggenburger</persName> &amp; Family<lb/>
                                        desire their kind regards to you.</p>
                    </body>
